  "instructions": "When we add 's' to verbs for He/She/It, we use the EXACT same sound rules we used for Plurals! It can make a sharp snake S, a buzzing bee Z, or an extra syllable IZ. Listen and repeat these 15 third-person verbs perfectly.",
  "contentItems": [
    {
      "type": "note",
      "text": "For words ending in vowels (like Go and See), the 'S' must vibrate like a 'Z'. He Go-zzz, not He Go-ss."
    }
  ],
